# Help: NVDIMM (persistent memory) block/namespace support
#
# The libnvdimm subsystem (LIBNVDIMM=m), claim infrastructure
# (ND_CLAIM), BTT (Block Translation Table for atomic sector
# semantics on byte-addressable pmem), and the DAX (direct
# access) fast-path for filesystem-level byte-addressable IO to
# persistent memory. ACPI_NFIT (the ACPI firmware interface that
# exposes NVDIMMs) lives in core/acpi-extras.config; layer that
# for a host-configured NVDIMM chain. NVDIMMs can also be exposed
# through virtio-pmem (virt/virtio-extras.config).
#
# NVDIMM_KEYS enables encrypted NVDIMM keyring support.
# NVDIMM_PFN maps pmem as PFN-backed memory for DAX. NVDIMM_DAX
# exposes /dev/daxN.M character devices.
#
# DAX=y and FS_DAX=y are also set by virt/virtio-fs.config
# (virtiofs DAX); the values match and merge_config only warns
# about redefinition. FS_DAX_PMD enables PMD-sized (2MiB) DAX
# faults.
# See: drivers/nvdimm/Kconfig
# See: drivers/dax/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/driver-api/nvdimm/nvdimm.html

CONFIG_LIBNVDIMM=m
CONFIG_ND_CLAIM=y
CONFIG_BTT=y
CONFIG_NVDIMM_PFN=y
CONFIG_NVDIMM_DAX=y
CONFIG_NVDIMM_KEYS=y
CONFIG_DAX=y
CONFIG_FS_DAX=y
CONFIG_FS_DAX_PMD=y
